      "content": "Grief over lost identity is profound when one's self-worth becomes intertwined with a life's work, especially when it felt sustained by others. Trying to force self-separation while feeling hollow often intensifies the pain, so please consider seeking support from a mental health professional to untangle these profound feelings. Remember that while this specific path collapsed, the scars or lessons endured by surviving it do not destroy the essence of the self anymore. It is dangerous to attempt suicide even when despair feels overwhelming; hurting yourself is a lie because death isn't death forever.",
